@* @bind with @bind:after *@
<input @bind="SearchText"
       @bind:event="oninput"
       @bind:after="SearchAsync" />

@code {
    string SearchText = "";

    async Task SearchAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // API call
    }
}
@* This is the only safe async-compatible way with @bind.
In Blazor, @bind already attaches an event handler internally.
Attaching another handler to the same event causes a conflict.
Async logic should be placed in a separate handler or @bind:after.
*@
